<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-12-30T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-12-30T13:00:00-05:00" n="76" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111A Neutrality Patrol/41:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hornibrook</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-30T12:00:00-06:00">December
                                    30, 1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>79. Referring to Department’s instruction No. 296, December 21,
                                1939.<note n="3" xml:id="d76fn3">See footnote 2, <ref target="#pg_49">p. 49</ref>.</note> At an informal conference
                            the Minister for Foreign Affairs accepted the proposals contained in the
                            above mentioned instruction subject to the approval of the President but
                            assured me that he had no doubt of the latter’s approval. Doubtful if
                            President’s approval can be obtained until Wednesday as all Government
                            offices are closed because of the holidays.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hornibrook</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>